Description: Rectangular limestone stela of Senusretseneb with a cornice at the top below which are two registers; upper: scene of the deceased seated with two women, loaded table inbetween, three rows of Hieroglyphic text above; lower: four kneeling figures and text.
Bibliographic references: Hall 1912 / Hieroglyphic texts from Egyptian stelae, etc., in the British Museum, Part 3. (pl.45)
